U.S. stocks pushed further into record heights on Friday following an encouraging report on hiring across the country. The S&P 500 closed higher, clinching an all-time high for the seventh straight day. The Dow Jones Industrial Average and the Nasdaq also rose.On Friday:The S&P 500 rose 17.47 points, or 0.4%, to 4,697.53.The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 203.72 points, or 0.6%, to 36,327.95.The Nasdaq rose 31.28 points, 0.2%, to 15,971.59.The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 34.65 points, or 1.4%, to 2,437.08.For the week:The S&P 500 is up 92.15 points, or 2%.The Dow is up 508.39 points, or 1.4%.The Nasdaq is up 473.20 points, or 3.1%.The Russell 2000 is up 139.89 points, or 6.1%.For the year:The S&P 500 is up 941.46 points, or 25.1%.The Dow is up 5,721.47 points, or 18.7%.The Nasdaq is up 3,083.31 points, or 23.9%.The Russell 2000 is up 462.23 points, or 23.4%.